[SN]TITLE[SN]
Merger of two rural schools in County Londonderry approved

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
An amalgamation of two schools in County Londonderry has been approved by Northern Ireland's education minister.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Rural maintained post-primaries St Mary's College in Clady and St Paul's College in Kilrea will merge when a new school building is completed.
John O'Dowd said the merger would create "one sustainable school".
The minister added that it would be capable of meeting the "educational needs, aptitudes, interests and aspirations" of pupils in the area.
